HEADWORD: Intertrigo
<hw>In`ter*tri"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>terere</ets>, <ets>tritum</ets>, to
rub.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A rubbing or chafing of the skin;
especially, an abrasion or excoriation of the skin between folds, as in
fat or neglected children.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intertrochanteric</ent>⟦br⟧
